{"word":"Deacon","slug":"deacon","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Deacon</b> An ecclesiastic charged with the temporal affairs of the church.<br/> Ordained by the apostles<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=44&chapter=6&verse=6'>Act 6:6</a><br/> Qualifications of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=54&chapter=3&verse=13'>1Ti 3:13</a><br/> Translated servant<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=40&chapter=23&verse=11'>Mat 23:11</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=43&chapter=12&verse=26'>Joh 12:26</a><br/> Translated minister<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=41&chapter=10&verse=43'>Mar 10:43</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=46&chapter=3&verse=5'>1Co 3:5</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=52&chapter=3&verse=2'>1Th 3:2</a>"}]}